cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a reinforcement learning-based approach for model compression. It also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it uses ImageNet dataset and measures the inference latency on an Android phone. Additionally, it involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it uses automated techniques for model compression. The paper also involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it compresses and accelerates neural network models. Finally, it may belong to the sub-category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it measures the speedup on a GPU.
